  • Method Details

    • GET

      public String GET(String table, int id, String data)
      Retrive a single entry from a CSV database row.
      Parameters:
      table - specified csv table in the csv database
      id - row id
      data - entry in the database, for example "Name" in employees.csv
      Returns:
      For example, GET("employees", 1, "Name") returns the name of the employee "John Doe"

    • UPDATE

      public String UPDATE(String table, int id, String field, String newValue)
      Update a fied value in the csv database with a new value
      Parameters:
      table - specified table in the csv database
      id - the id of the row
      field - entry in the database, for example "Name" in employees.csv
      newValue - the value to replace field with
      Returns:
      For example, UPDATE("employees", 1, "Name", "Johnathan Doe") updates the name of the employee "John Doe" to "Johnathan Doe"

    • GET_ROW

      public HashMap<String,String> GET_ROW(String table, int id, String date)
      Returns a whole row from a specified table in hashmap form
      Parameters:
      table - specified table in the csv database
      id - the id of the row
      date - date associated with record only used for payslip retrieval
      Returns:
      A HashMap<String, String> where the keys are column names and the values are the corresponding data. Returns null if the record is not found.

    • GET_COL

      public ArrayList<String> GET_COL(String table, String column)
      Retrives a specific column from a csv file in the database
      Parameters:
      table - specified table in the csv database
      column - the column of the csv that is requested
      Returns:
      ArrayList of all data under the specified column

    • GET_CSV

      public ArrayList<HashMap<String,String>> GET_CSV(String table)
      Returns entire csv table in the form of an Arraylist of Hashmaps. Each hashmap represents a row in the csv
      Parameters:
      table - specified table in the csv database
      Returns:
      ArrayList<HashMap<String, String>> of the entire csv file, where each HasMap<String, String> represents a row in key:value pair

    • ADD

      public boolean ADD(String table, String[] data)
      Method used to add entries to a csv file
      Parameters:
      table - specified table in the csv database
      data - data for all columns to add to a row
      Returns:
      If that data has been added successfully to the csv

    • LATEST_ROW

      public HashMap<String,String> LATEST_ROW(String table)

      Returns:
